First time I ever watched Anjelah Johnson and did not find her funny. In all fairness, I did not watch the show to the end, it was so awful. I love her as Bonquiqui and the young woman going to a Vietnamese nail salon. maybe it got better, but, life is too short to watch a boring unfunny entertainer.

She has such great expressions.  Very funny.  I didn't get all of her references, not being Latina, but it didn't matter.  And, unlike most comics, nothing vulgar!

I'm not sure why this sad excuse for a comedy special has four stars... I'm sure she's a very nice woman, but frankly, I can't figure out who thought that she deserved her own comedy special ...  Ms. Johnson is about as funny as your younger sister telling a somewhat boring story at a family dinner (and to be honest, I'm not sure that she would qualify even to that low of a standard ).  She spends far too much time talking about herself (not in a generalized way as lead-ins to larger issues and subjects) but literally just about herself....  frankly, she doesn't belong in the ranks of professional comedians for one very simple issue....her timing is terrible.

I love all types of comedy from any type of comedian... as long as they look like they've done it professionally for period of time and earned their chops.

Let's put it this way... I got this free on Amazon prime and I still turned it off before the end because I just couldn't take it anymore.

Spend your time listening to somebody that has EARNED their comedy chops like Bill Burr, Maz Jobrani or any one of several dozen other great comedians out there.

Anjelah shows her truly awesome comedic talent  in this incredibly funny comedy show and she manages to pull it off with the greatest of ease while using absolutely no vulgarity and almost no profanity which is so refreshing to see but almost non-existent in a modern comedian! I've seen Anjelah do her concert routine on T.V. Having seen her earlier DVD, I couldn't wait to see "Homecoming Show'. She saves the best for last , when she talks about going out for a taco at 10 o'clock at night. Her facial expressions are priceless. I only wish this show was longer, it's only 60 minutes, not counting bonus features If you loved Tammy and the "Nail Salon", from "That's How We Do It", you'll love "Homecoming Show".
Loved it. Love her brand of comedy. Had me laughing so much it hurt! A must see if you love to laugh!
